description: All Kansas Future/Current Boat Owners Please Read If you live in Kansas you need to know this about boat ownership. -Any boat bought from any INDIVIDUAL no matter what state or country they live in, per Kansas law there is NO SALES TAX to be paid to the state or County Treasurer. If you buy a new or used boat from a boat dealer in state or out of state, you are asked to pay the sales tax to either the dealer or County Treasurer. Sales tax is around 9% and varies around the state. -Boat property tax is now 5%, was 30% two years ago. -Kansas does not title boats (watercraft) or engines for marine use. -Trailers carrying under 2000 pounds are not required to be registered but is a good idea to list the trailer on your annual property tax statement. When questioned, many boat dealers in both Kansas and Missouri act like they are not aware of not paying any sales tax for boats purchased from individuals. Please tell your Kansas boating friends about this law.
title: Current/Future Kansas Boat Owners, Please Read, Pay No Sales Tax
